Companies in the European Union
could save 40 billion euros ($53 billion) a year if the EU
reduced bureaucratic procedures, Die Welt reported, citing a
report from a group led by the former Bavarian Prime Minister
Edmund Stoiber.  Stoiber will present the report to European Commission
President  Jose Barroso  on Feb. 21, Die Welt said. Stoiber is the
